## Context

This is Task 1 of 10 in the macOS UI Automation Hardening plan. The core problem: `sendKeyCombo` currently sends modifier keys as separate CGEvent key events but does NOT set `CGEventFlags` on the main key event. Many apps (Xcode, etc.) check flags rather than individual key events, so key combos like Cmd+Shift+O are silently ignored.

The fix sets `keyDown.flags = flags` on the main key event AND keeps sending individual modifier key events for backward compatibility. A `defer` block ensures modifier keys are always released.

The project uses Node built-in test runner (not Jest), `withClient()` helper pattern, and `extractText()` to get text from MCP tool results.

